Refactor progress bar update logic and clean up duplicated code
Enhanced progress bar update by modifying the calculation and update logic. Now, it accurately calculates the progress as a percentage and stores it as an integer, improving performance. This update applies across multiple files. Redundant code lines were also eliminated for a cleaner, more readable code.

- feat(ui): refactor and enhance UI layouts and fonts for consistency
- Replaced Times New Roman with Damascus font across all UI components for unified visual style - Increased default font size to 11pt to improve readability - Standardized UI layout grid structure and spacing in `Inv_Materiali.ui`, `Tma.ui`, and `US_USM.ui` - Reorganized form elements for logical grouping and better user experience - Updated component naming and properties for clarity and accessibility - Enabled antialiasing and pointer feedback (cursor and mouse tracking) on all fields - Improved form modal behavior and control sizing for responsive display - Removed redundant stylesheet definitions and cleaned up XML formatting in `.ui` files - Introduced new input fields and refined labels for better form clarity and semantics - refactor(ui): simplify layout and remove deprecated fields from form
- Removed unused QLineEdit widgets for internal, general, and international catalog numbers - Replaced complex palette and font declarations with simplified styles - Updated tooltips and labels for clarity and consistency - Changed "Quadrato/Parete" label to "Area" - Replaced static sector combo box with editable area field - Consolidated unita tipo and site fields into more user-friendly combo boxes - Removed unnecessary spacers and grid items to reduce UI clutter - Enhanced layout consistency by applying uniform styling and mouse tracking settings - feat: update UI layout and localization for stratigraphic unit form
- Added support for new font styling using Damascus with updated point sizes - Reorganized multiple QPushButton, QLabel, and QLineEdit widgets for better UI alignment - Introduced new tooltips for enhanced usability and interaction clarity - Updated element naming conventions for clarity and consistency - Removed unused or deprecated widgets and repositioned existing ones - Separated stratigraphic relation tabs into distinct logical groups - Enhanced mouse tracking and context menu policies for interactive elements - Replaced Times New Roman with Damascus font across the form - Improved layout grid structure for better scalability and maintenance - Introduced collapsible group boxes to manage complex forms - Updated icons for record navigation and action buttons for visual enhancement - feat(tma): add support for repeating material data and enhanced thesaurus syncing
- Added new table `tma_materiali_ripetibili` to support repeating material components linked to TMA records - Modified UI to correctly load, display, and save materials from the new table structure - Updated PDF export to show full material details including category, class, typology, and chronology - Updated thesaurus mappings to support precise field-level definitions for compiled records - Removed deprecated spatial table creation at module load time for improved database compatibility - Fixed database creation logic to support PostgreSQL initialization with proper signal handling - Improved error handling and debug logging in database migration, import, and insertion flows - Synced tipologia list in Inventario Materiali form to use TMA material thesaurus (code 10.12) for standardization

feat(ui): enhance TMA form layout and materials management; remove debug logs
- refactor: redesigned TMA form layout using improved grid structures for better scalability and UX - feat: introduced collapsible group boxes and updated font to Damascus with 11pt size for visual consistency - feat: added new editable fields, improved tooltips, and reorganized form elements for logical grouping - feat: added new "TMA materiali" tab to support repeating material entries with enhanced table support - chore: removed deprecated widgets and layout elements to reduce clutter - refactor: simplified stylesheet usage and removed redundant definitions across UI - fix: relocated log file output to system temp directory for compatibility - chore: removed all debug logging from TMA module, tests, and related files for production readiness - fix: adjusted navigation and material persistence logic for improved data handling and database integrity - chore: cleaned up XML and Python code formatting for maintainability and readability

chore: add pass statements to replace removed debug logs and fix empty code blocks
Refactored several locations in pyarchinit_db_manager.py and Tma.py by adding pass statements where debug logs were previously present or to handle empty code blocks, ensuring code clarity and avoiding syntax errors.

chore(schema): increase varchar length for excavation-related fields
- Updated `pyarchinit_schema_clean.sql` and `pyarchinit_schema_updated.sql` to increase the character limits of various fields from short lengths (e.g., 20, 30, 45) to 255 - Fields affected include: `anno_scavo`, `metodo_di_scavo`, `data_schedatura`, `schedatore`, `formazione`, `stato_di_conservazione`, `colore`, `consistenza`, `struttura`, and `cont_per` - Change ensures better compatibility with longer text inputs and improves data flexibility across multiple excavation and material record entries

feat(thesaurus): implement unique constraints and duplication cleanup
- Added a new button and handler (`on_pushButton_apply_constraints_pressed`) to apply unique constraints to the `pyarchinit_thesaurus_sigle` table for both PostgreSQL and SQLite backends - Cleaned up trailing spaces across thesaurus fields before constraint application - Implemented logic to detect and remove existing duplicate records based on composite unique keys - Enforced unique constraints on combinations of `lingua`, `nome_tabella`, `tipologia_sigla`, and `sigla_estesa` or `sigla` - Modified data import logic to check for existing thesaurus records and update them instead of inserting duplicates - Updated schema definitions in `pyarchinit_schema_clean.sql` and model class in `Pyarchinit_thesaurus_sigle.py` accordingly - Enhanced import UI and toolbar in `Inv_Materiali.ui` and `Tma.ui` for better interaction and data clarity - Added test and helper scripts for validating and fixing thesaurus data integrity
BREAKING CHANGE: Existing duplicates in the thesaurus table must be resolved before applying constraints. Existing import workflows relying on duplicate records may be affected.

feat(thesaurus): add optional unique constraint logic and conflict analysis script
- Commented out optional unique constraint on `sigla` to prevent errors in presence of duplicate short codes - Added inline guidance on usage of the second constraint for PostgreSQL - Introduced `analyze_sigla_conflicts.py` to help identify and resolve duplicates before constraint enforcement - Supports cleaner constraint application and smooth transition for legacy thesaurus data
BREAKING CHANGE: Enabling the second constraint without resolving existing duplicates may cause migration failures.

feat(thesaurus): improve import logic with duplicate handling and optional constraints
- Updated thesaurus data import logic to skip existing records instead of overwriting them - Wrapped new record insertions in try/except blocks to silently ignore constraint violations such as duplicates - Adjusted logic to enhance compatibility with optional unique constraints on `sigla` - Refined `LAST_COMMIT_MESSAGE` to reflect new constraint guidance and utility scripts - Added `clean_source_thesaurus.py` to aid in data normalization before constraint enforcement
BREAKING CHANGE: Existing import workflows may skip duplicate records instead of updating them; ensure data consistency prior to import.

feat(thesaurus,tma): add inventory export tools and enhance thesaurus compatibility
- Added A5 PDF export feature for Inventario schede with customizable headers and image support - Introduced Excel export for TMA crate list with materials summary grouped by magazzino and cassa - Extended `PYARCHINIT_THESAURUS_SIGLE` model to support `n_tipologia` and `n_sigla` fields - Ensured compatibility with optional thesaurus table naming variations and multilingual support - Improved debug logging for thesaurus field loading and fallback scenarios - Added SQL fallback for missing columns in thesaurus table - UI updates to support export buttons in Inventario and TMA interface - BREAKING CHANGE: New thesaurus fields (`n_tipologia`, `n_sigla`) required for full feature support; run migration script if updating existing installations

feat(tma): introduce table view and advanced search capabilities
- Added a new tabbed "Vista Tabella" (Table View) interface to TMA module for browsing records in a sortable table - Implemented double-click loading of TMA records from table view into form view - Introduced "Ricerca Avanzata" (Advanced Search) dialog for querying TMA entries by US ranges and cassetta values - Enhanced UI with toolbar buttons for quick access to advanced search and table view - Improved usability by dynamically injecting UI elements and preserving existing layout - Refactored tab management to support live data reloading on tab switch - Minor internal logging and error handling improvements for UI actions

fix(connection): remove deprecated sslmode parameter from connection string
- Removed "?sslmode=allow" from PostgreSQL connection strings to prevent compatibility issues with modern drivers - Ensured masked connection strings match updated format - Minor import cleanup in US_USM module to include missing datetime import for future use - Updated workspace metadata with latest commit message and task tracking changes

feat: add logic to update TMA records when reperto is removed from inventory
- Implemented update_tma_inventario_field method to synchronize TMA 'inventario' field when a reperto is added or removed - Hooked into delete operations to remove references to deleted reperti from related TMA records - Improved centroid calculation for stratigraph

feat: add HTML escaping for descriptions and improve inventory field handling with US ranges
- Introduced `escape_html` static method to safely render user-provided descriptions in PDF output. - Updated `pyarchinit_exp_USsheet_pdf.py` to use HTML escaping for description fields. - Enhanced `Tma.py` to support US ranges (e.g., "3200-3201") when querying inventory materials. - Improved logging for debugging including materials found, US parsing, and fallback scenarios. - Added error logging with traceback to aid in diagnosing issues during inventory field updates.

feat(concurrency): add PostgreSQL user sync, permission checks, and record versioning
- Automatically create PostgreSQL users with role-based permissions when PyArchInit users are saved - Synchronize permissions from PyArchInit permission table to PostgreSQL GRANTs - Add support for record versioning and concurrency fields (e.g., version_number, editing_by, last_modified_by) - Add auto-refresh interval to check for concurrent record modifications across forms - Show user-friendly conflict resolution dialog when records are updated externally - Improve error handling with permission-based feedback for UPDATE/INSERT operations - Disable manual editing of computed fields like 'datazione', auto-update via triggers or form logic - Include database username in session for accurate tracking and permissions - Refactor trigger logic for proper privilege checks during automated updates of related records - Introduce permission handler and concurrency manager modules for modular access control logic

feat(text2sql): support multiple LLMs including OpenAI GPT-4 and Ollama
- Replaced old text2sql.ai API with OpenAI GPT-4 integration using local API key - Added support for local models via Ollama with dynamic model selection - Refactored UI to allow selecting between OpenAI, Ollama, and placeholder for free API - Modularized SQL generation and explanation logic for each mode - Improved schema-to-text conversion with spatial notes for better prompt context - Removed legacy local model download and management code - Ensured backward compatibility by keeping legacy function names as wrappers - Updated workspace configuration and removed obsolete Python breakpoints

feat(db-updater): add automatic PostgreSQL and SQLite schema alignment tools
- Implemented automatic schema check and update for both PostgreSQL and SQLite databases - Added `postgres_db_updater.py` and `sqlite_db_updater.py` for validation and patching of outdated schema - Integrated update logic into `pyarchinit_db_manager.py` for seamless schema verification on connection - Enabled "Update Postgres DB" button by default in configuration dialog - Added utility scripts for verifying, fixing, and restoring database structures - Updated thesaurus schema with new constraints and hierarchy fields - Improved S3DGraphy export with integrated DOT/GraphML output using `s3dgraphy_dot_bridge.py` for yEd compatibility - Included backup files and migration scripts for KTM24 and Sant'Arcangelo database alignment

feat(db): add quota column to reperti table and update schema
- Added `quota` column to `pyarchinit_reperti` table in SQLite and PostgreSQL schemas - Updated associated views to include the `quota` field - Implemented schema update logic in `postgres_db_updater.py` and `sqlite_db_updater.py` - Adjusted GUI to disable PostgreSQL update button when access is restricted - Included view recreation logic for ensuring `quota` integration

feat(import): implement media-to-entity ID mapping for import process
- Added MediaMigrationMapper utility to manage and track ID mappings during data import - Integrated ID mapping logic into the import process for multiple tables (US, INVENTARIO_MATERIALI, POTTERY, STRUTTURA, TOMBA, TMA, MEDIA) - Ensured imported MEDIA records correctly reference newly generated entity IDs - Updated user messages to display ID mapping summary after import - Improved consistency and traceability of media associations across imported entities
